<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1920-08-16T17:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1920-08-16T17:36:00-05:00" n="890" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d890">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">818.6363/51: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Consul at San José</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Chase</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                    State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">San
                                            José</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1920-08-16T17:00:00-05:36"><hi rend="italic">August
                                            16, 1920—5 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received August 17—8:55
                                    a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>56. My telegram number 40, July 19, 6 p.m. Resolution quoted passed
                                Congress this afternoon again by more than two thirds after the
                                President had refused to act upon it.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Chase</hi></signed></closer>
